text.section:
A contract made pursuant to a telephone solicitation:
Shall be reduced to writing and signed by the consumer;
Shall comply with all other applicable laws and regulations;
Shall match the description of goods or services as that principally used in the telephone solicitation;
Shall contain the name, address, and telephone number of the seller, the total price of the contract, and a detailed description of the goods or services being sold;
Shall contain, in at least 12 point type, immediately preceding the signature, the following statement:
May not exclude from its terms any oral or written representations made by the merchant to the consumer in connection with the transaction.
